WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.936 --> 00:00:04.469
           <i> Previously</i>
 <i> on</i> The Bastard Executioner...

2
00:00:04.471 --> 00:00:06.771
          (screaming)

3
00:00:06.773 --> 00:00:07.938
                         BERBER:
           There are many things

4
00:00:07.940 --> 00:00:10.173
we do not know about our leader.

5
00:00:10.175 --> 00:00:11.440
        Even Petra knows
       little of his life

6
00:00:11.442 --> 00:00:13.275
  <i> before he came to the river.</i>

7
00:00:13.277 --> 00:00:15.143
Will you ever
tell me what you see?

8
00:00:15.145 --> 00:00:17.011
ANGEL CHILD AND ANNORA:
Your savior needs you

9
00:00:17.013 --> 00:00:19.113
        to live the life
      of a different man.

10
00:00:19.115 --> 00:00:21.115
                            MAN:
                  Gawain Maddox!

11
00:00:21.117 --> 00:00:22.883
         The traveling punisher.
Ah.

12
00:00:22.885 --> 00:00:24.985
     This is half my wage.

13
00:00:24.987 --> 00:00:26.886
If you do not find this
satisfactory.

14
00:00:26.888 --> 00:00:28.454
                        move on.

15
00:00:28.456 --> 00:00:30.322
                  Time is a most
          aggressive foe. Milus.

16
00:00:30.324 --> 00:00:31.823
    I need to make my gains now.

17
00:00:31.825 --> 00:00:33.324
       <i> We need to fortify</i>
         <i> our resources.</i>

18
00:00:33.326 --> 00:00:35.959
   <i> Steeper taxes and tariffs.</i>

19
00:00:35.961 --> 00:00:37.393
LADY LOVE:
You will break them. Milus.

20
00:00:37.395 --> 00:00:38.894
        And we both know
 there's nothing more dangerous

21
00:00:38.896 --> 00:00:41.062
        than a Welshman
    who has nothing to lose.

22
00:00:41.064 --> 00:00:42.663
       Tell me. Baroness.

23
00:00:42.665 --> 00:00:44.798
     <i> How is it that someone</i>
       <i> of your privilege</i>

24
00:00:44.800 --> 00:00:47.634
        <i> may come to know</i>
 <i> the plight of the common man?</i>

25
00:00:47.636 --> 00:00:49.836
                   It is time.

26
00:00:49.838 --> 00:00:51.304
TORAN:
Brother Wilk.

27
00:00:51.306 --> 00:00:52.471
      Ventris comes again.
                        Already?

28
00:00:52.473 --> 00:00:53.572
JACOB:<i> They'll take what little</i>

29
00:00:53.574 --> 00:00:55.740
stock and harvest we have left.

30
00:00:55.742 --> 00:00:57.241
 We can't do this without you.

31
00:00:57.243 --> 00:00:59.076
              Yea.

32
00:00:59.078 --> 00:01:00.744
     Gather supplies. We'll need
          to ride before midday.

33
00:01:00.746 --> 00:01:03.747
             PETRA:
  <i> You're not a rebel. Wilkin.</i>

34
00:01:03.749 --> 00:01:05.682
  JONAS:<i> Took us in darkness. </i>
           (laughter)

35
00:01:05.684 --> 00:01:06.649
         Deadly ghosts.

36
00:01:06.651 --> 00:01:07.883
       <i> In familiar hoods.</i>

37
00:01:07.885 --> 00:01:08.884
  <i> There was another this time.</i>

38
00:01:08.886 --> 00:01:10.552
    <i> Saw a flash of his face.</i>

39
00:01:10.554 --> 00:01:13.021
             PETRA:
   <i> Ventris is sly and brutal.</i>

40
00:01:13.023 --> 00:01:15.423
       It's only time and chance
      before you feel his blade.

41
00:01:15.425 --> 00:01:16.557
       We've barely stock
       and food to live.

42
00:01:16.559 --> 00:01:18.358
           You're the only stock

43
00:01:18.360 --> 00:01:20.760
           I can't live without!

44
00:01:20.762 --> 00:01:23.763
  Is there a mind for fairness
     in your swift purpose?

45
00:01:23.765 --> 00:01:25.097
      Of course. my love.

46
00:01:25.099 --> 00:01:27.265
  Fair process for every man.

47
00:01:27.267 --> 00:01:28.532
We can't do this alone anymore.

48
00:01:28.534 --> 00:01:30.400
   <i> You saw the daffodil hides</i>
         <i> in the trees.</i>

49
00:01:30.402 --> 00:01:31.901
     The Byth Encil rebels

50
00:01:31.903 --> 00:01:32.835
    would welcome our skill.

51
00:01:32.837 --> 00:01:34.603
       VENTRIS:<i> Where are</i>

52
00:01:34.605 --> 00:01:36.271
your men?!

53
00:01:36.273 --> 00:01:37.505
 They went to Glen Darby Birch.

54
00:01:37.507 --> 00:01:38.706
       With their hoods?

55
00:01:38.708 --> 00:01:40.040
                Yea! With hoods!

56
00:01:40.042 --> 00:01:43.008
        (Eva screaming)

57
00:01:44.011 --> 00:01:45.076
            VENTRIS:
         <i> Kill them all.</i>

58
00:01:46.079 --> 00:01:47.344
     <i> Burn it to the ground.</i>

59
00:01:49.247 --> 00:01:51.313
        What are you...?

60
00:02:01.190 --> 00:02:03.256
        (fire crackling)

61
00:02:06.727 --> 00:02:07.726
            (shouts)

62
00:02:07.728 --> 00:02:09.527
                        (groans)
Careful. boy.

63
00:02:09.529 --> 00:02:12.596
                    S-Sorry. Ma.
                        (groans)

64
00:02:18.236 --> 00:02:21.370
        It's shit. Hmm?

65
00:02:21.372 --> 00:02:23.238
      Like the lot of you.

66
00:02:23.240 --> 00:02:25.707
Come here.
         I'm-I'm sorry.

67
00:02:25.709 --> 00:02:28.076
         (baby crying)
Don't mother him.

68
00:02:28.078 --> 00:02:31.045
   He needs to feel the pain
        of his mistake.

69
00:02:31.047 --> 00:02:32.813
JESSAMY:
He feels it.

70
00:02:32.815 --> 00:02:35.649
        I won't tend it.

71
00:02:35.651 --> 00:02:38.985
    Please. enjoy the drink.

72
00:02:38.987 --> 00:02:40.886
     We have another bird.

73
00:02:40.888 --> 00:02:42.721
                   I'll feed you
                       in short.

74
00:02:42.723 --> 00:02:45.123
Don't put rule on me. whore!
 (groans)

75
00:02:46.826 --> 00:02:48.492
                    No. (crying)

76
00:02:48.494 --> 00:02:49.826
Crawl. you cur!

77
00:02:49.828 --> 00:02:51.394
                        JESSAMY:
                  Please. Maddy.

78
00:02:51.396 --> 00:02:53.229
                         GAWAIN:
             Show me the trench.

79
00:02:59.737 --> 00:03:01.236
          The village!

80
00:03:01.238 --> 00:03:03.671
                           Hyah!
                        (shouts)

81
00:03:08.076 --> 00:03:09.475
                  (horse neighs)

82
00:03:17.851 --> 00:03:20.518
(Wilkin groans)

83
00:03:20.520 --> 00:03:23.187
(shuddering breaths)

84
00:03:23.189 --> 00:03:24.521
              No.

85
00:03:24.523 --> 00:03:27.190
           (panting)

86
00:03:27.192 --> 00:03:29.258
              No.

87
00:03:29.260 --> 00:03:31.326
(crying)

88
00:03:36.533 --> 00:03:38.833
            (crying)

89
00:03:58.386 --> 00:04:00.452
           (panting)

90
00:04:08.628 --> 00:04:11.295
                 (crying softly)

91
00:04:11.297 --> 00:04:13.196
          Dear child.

92
00:04:19.336 --> 00:04:20.868
           (panting)

93
00:04:26.308 --> 00:04:28.374
             Oh...

94
00:04:42.923 --> 00:04:44.923
                          (sobs)

95
00:04:44.925 --> 00:04:47.392
           Sweet boy.

96
00:04:51.764 --> 00:04:54.164
            My Rhys.

97
00:04:58.870 --> 00:05:01.370
               This was Ventris.

98
00:05:01.372 --> 00:05:03.705
    His collector as proof!

99
00:05:03.707 --> 00:05:06.274
         Savage noble!

100
00:05:11.914 --> 00:05:14.614
    Damn your holy destiny.

101
00:05:19.019 --> 00:05:21.919
           (sobbing):
    Devil Christ. Damn you.

102
00:05:44.042 --> 00:05:46.108
           (grunting)

103
00:05:59.822 --> 00:06:01.988
           (panting)

104
00:06:11.465 --> 00:06:13.531
                        (grunts)

105
00:06:16.736 --> 00:06:18.501
             JACOB:
           The sword.

106
00:06:20.605 --> 00:06:23.172
      Crest of Edward the First.

107
00:06:27.578 --> 00:06:28.977
            (grunts)

108
00:06:28.979 --> 00:06:31.079
             CALO:
      Where does he ride?

109
00:06:31.081 --> 00:06:33.114
To meet the devil.

110
00:06:33.116 --> 00:06:35.583
                      As are we.

111
00:06:35.585 --> 00:06:37.318
        Our families...

112
00:06:37.320 --> 00:06:39.320
        Will be avenged.

113
00:06:39.322 --> 00:06:41.188
         (horse neighs)
              Hup!

114
00:06:41.190 --> 00:06:43.256
                     (grunts)

115
00:06:54.368 --> 00:06:56.701
        See to the dead.

116
00:06:56.703 --> 00:06:58.269
       This is my fight.

117
00:06:58.271 --> 00:07:01.071
 We've all earned this horror.

118
00:07:05.810 --> 00:07:09.344
  I've no plan but vengeance.

119
00:07:09.346 --> 00:07:12.080
      The only plan left.

120
00:07:23.492 --> 00:07:25.124
           Yea. then.

121
00:07:25.126 --> 00:07:26.959
       To Castle Ventris.

122
00:07:26.961 --> 00:07:28.560
         (horse neighs)
              Ha!

123
00:07:31.464 --> 00:07:33.530
           (shouting)

124
00:07:55.353 --> 00:07:58.020
         This is mine.

125
00:07:58.022 --> 00:08:00.088
      (shuddering breaths)

126
00:08:02.692 --> 00:08:04.391
            My due.

127
00:08:04.393 --> 00:08:07.560
           My sorrow.

128
00:08:13.868 --> 00:08:15.267
          Forgive me.

129
00:08:17.404 --> 00:08:19.470
   (sizzling. quiet gasping)

130
00:08:23.842 --> 00:08:25.908
       (panting. sobbing)

131
00:08:30.380 --> 00:08:35.749
     ♪ Born with a heart ♪

132
00:08:35.751 --> 00:08:40.086
       ♪ That could ache
        more than beat ♪

133
00:08:42.757 --> 00:08:47.693
    ♪ The mind of a killer ♪

134
00:08:48.729 --> 00:08:52.764
    ♪ The soul of the meek ♪

135
00:08:55.034 --> 00:08:59.437
   ♪ Flock with no shepherd ♪

136
00:09:00.473 --> 00:09:04.141
    ♪ Is a vulnerable game ♪

137
00:09:07.045 --> 00:09:09.879
          ♪ I can live
       without a hearth ♪

138
00:09:09.881 --> 00:09:13.215
        ♪ Without love ♪

139
00:09:13.217 --> 00:09:17.485
    ♪ But I do need a name ♪

140
00:09:19.922 --> 00:09:22.589
    ♪ Father. do you burn ♪

141
00:09:22.591 --> 00:09:26.025
  ♪ If your hand is in fire? ♪

142
00:09:26.027 --> 00:09:29.161
        ♪ Does your head
        spin with rage ♪

143
00:09:29.163 --> 00:09:32.664
 ♪ When fooled by the liars? ♪

144
00:09:32.666 --> 00:09:35.767
     ♪ King of the kings ♪

145
00:09:38.238 --> 00:09:43.140
   ♪ Do you feel any pain? ♪

146
00:09:44.409 --> 00:09:49.645
   ♪ Do you feel any pain? ♪

147
00:10:02.859 --> 00:10:04.925
         (crows cawing)

148
00:10:08.596 --> 00:10:11.096
           The witch.

149
00:10:18.304 --> 00:10:20.304
  What brings you so far east.

150
00:10:20.306 --> 00:10:22.139
                          woman?

151
00:10:22.141 --> 00:10:25.075
The same thing
that brings all of you.

152
00:10:25.077 --> 00:10:27.410
We flee the darkness.

153
00:10:27.412 --> 00:10:29.912
 Did you witness the massacre?

154
00:10:29.914 --> 00:10:31.914
              No.

155
00:10:31.916 --> 00:10:36.317
    But I will witness yours
 unless you alter your purpose.

156
00:10:36.319 --> 00:10:39.253
   There's nothing to alter.

157
00:10:39.255 --> 00:10:40.988
     We face what's ahead.

158
00:10:40.990 --> 00:10:45.925
      But you do not need
       to face it alone.

159
00:10:45.927 --> 00:10:50.562
    Your cynic-- he has ties
     to the way of victory.

160
00:11:00.573 --> 00:11:04.240
  You are all knots and coil.

161
00:11:04.242 --> 00:11:05.741
                       (inhales)

162
00:11:05.743 --> 00:11:08.577
      Pain of yesterday's
         fierce effort.

163
00:11:08.579 --> 00:11:10.011
         (sighs softly)

164
00:11:11.948 --> 00:11:14.315
So you found your bandits.

165
00:11:14.317 --> 00:11:16.283
                             No.

166
00:11:16.285 --> 00:11:19.318
             But we met with the
           proof of their guilt.

167
00:11:21.255 --> 00:11:23.255
      And you've returned
        with that proof?

168
00:11:23.257 --> 00:11:25.790
                      (chuckles)

169
00:11:25.792 --> 00:11:28.759
              Difficult to carry
                  bone and slag.

170
00:11:28.761 --> 00:11:29.960
          (door opens)

171
00:11:29.962 --> 00:11:32.095
                        CORBETT:
                        My lord.

172
00:11:32.097 --> 00:11:34.263
       A scout came through from
          midshire this morning.

173
00:11:34.265 --> 00:11:36.965
       Spotted seven men
   traveling east last night.

174
00:11:36.967 --> 00:11:39.801
        One with a sword
   bearing Longshanks' mark.

175
00:11:39.803 --> 00:11:41.803
                Our bandits on a
               mission. perhaps.

176
00:11:41.805 --> 00:11:44.272
     Taking their vengeance
          to my gate?

177
00:11:44.274 --> 00:11:46.641
 Are they that mad with grief?

178
00:11:46.643 --> 00:11:50.144
Or soldiers willing to die
in service of their sorrow.

179
00:11:50.146 --> 00:11:52.312
I think it best
we meet them in journey.

180
00:11:52.314 --> 00:11:55.648
  away from anyone who may see
   this fool play as valiant.

181
00:11:55.650 --> 00:11:57.116
                           Stay.

182
00:11:57.118 --> 00:11:59.284
              Protect the walls.

183
00:11:59.286 --> 00:12:01.052
     Prepare a full legion
       of foot soldiers.

184
00:12:01.054 --> 00:12:03.354
 I'll gut this warrior bandit.

185
00:12:03.356 --> 00:12:06.023
  Choke him cold with a snare
      of his own entrails.

186
00:12:06.025 --> 00:12:08.091
A fine plan. my lord.

187
00:12:11.729 --> 00:12:14.196
Are you waiting
for a royal proclamation?

188
00:12:14.198 --> 00:12:15.830
Go with him. Reeve.

189
00:12:15.832 --> 00:12:18.065
                    Yes. indeed.
                    Chamberlain.

190
00:12:18.067 --> 00:12:19.566
                        My lady.

191
00:12:28.676 --> 00:12:30.742
               (horses neighing)

192
00:12:43.856 --> 00:12:46.189
     Who are you. traveler?

193
00:12:46.191 --> 00:12:48.191
     Gawain Maddox. milord.

194
00:12:48.193 --> 00:12:49.926
   I come up from the South.

195
00:12:49.928 --> 00:12:51.761
       Punisher by trade.

196
00:12:51.763 --> 00:12:53.763
 You have tools in possession?

197
00:12:53.765 --> 00:12:55.364
                         Yea'on.

198
00:12:55.366 --> 00:12:56.732
         Ride with us.

199
00:12:56.734 --> 00:12:59.367
I may need
your services.

200
00:12:59.369 --> 00:13:01.702
           My family.

201
00:13:01.704 --> 00:13:03.203
Ride the main trail north.

202
00:13:03.205 --> 00:13:05.171
It leads to Castle Ventris.

203
00:13:05.173 --> 00:13:07.239
They can wait there.

204
00:13:09.176 --> 00:13:11.176
Just follow on.

205
00:13:11.178 --> 00:13:13.244
I'll be with you.

206
00:13:19.584 --> 00:13:21.650
      (horses sputtering)

207
00:13:34.898 --> 00:13:38.799
      Do you remember me.
        Earl Constable?

208
00:13:40.736 --> 00:13:42.802
         I'm the knight
     you sent to his death

209
00:13:42.804 --> 00:13:46.104
          at the hands
     of the hoarding Scots.

210
00:13:47.073 --> 00:13:49.039
          Impossible.

211
00:13:49.041 --> 00:13:52.575
  You know this man. my lord?

212
00:13:52.577 --> 00:13:55.978
               If you are indeed
                    that knight.

213
00:13:55.980 --> 00:13:59.581
                 you're either a
            deserter or a ghost.

214
00:13:59.583 --> 00:14:03.050
               If not dead then.

215
00:14:03.052 --> 00:14:05.118
         then dead now.

216
00:14:10.792 --> 00:14:14.793
     I live with the terror
  of your betrayal every day.

217
00:14:17.497 --> 00:14:21.432
 But I'll spare you that pain.

218
00:14:21.434 --> 00:14:24.401
  Death will quiet your mind.

219
00:14:33.444 --> 00:14:35.543
They're all rebels. milord.

220
00:14:37.847 --> 00:14:41.248
    Time to go back to hell.
         Marcher Baron!

221
00:14:42.117 --> 00:14:43.449
           (whistles)

222
00:14:43.451 --> 00:14:44.716
       (horses neighing)

223
00:14:48.821 --> 00:14:50.787
           <i> Deus vult!</i>

224
00:14:50.789 --> 00:14:52.355
         (men shouting)

225
00:15:15.780 --> 00:15:17.746
            (yells)

226
00:15:47.010 --> 00:15:48.242
                     Go. go. go!

227
00:15:51.913 --> 00:15:53.479
           (screams)

228
00:15:57.184 --> 00:15:59.083
            (neighs)

229
00:16:17.936 --> 00:16:19.335
            (grunts)

230
00:16:35.518 --> 00:16:36.783
           (screams)

231
00:17:07.782 --> 00:17:11.783
    Not ghost. nor deserter.

232
00:17:11.785 --> 00:17:14.685
           Nor hood.

233
00:17:20.459 --> 00:17:22.192
(yells)

234
00:17:30.635 --> 00:17:32.301
            (yells)

235
00:17:39.309 --> 00:17:40.374
            (yells)

236
00:17:53.788 --> 00:17:55.487
            VENTRIS:
     London will hunt down

237
00:17:55.489 --> 00:17:59.023
       the hooded bandits
 and crush your toy rebellion.

238
00:17:59.025 --> 00:18:01.191
       I've no rebellion.

239
00:18:01.193 --> 00:18:03.092
  Just a need to see you die.

240
00:18:06.663 --> 00:18:07.762
                         (yells)

241
00:18:25.348 --> 00:18:27.414
              ♪ ♪

242
00:18:59.714 --> 00:19:02.414
                      How is he?
                   Will he heal?

243
00:19:02.416 --> 00:19:06.250
Only blood runs.
no other humors.

244
00:19:06.252 --> 00:19:08.318
He will sleep.

245
00:19:16.227 --> 00:19:18.393
                         BERBER:
              Ventris was right.

246
00:19:18.395 --> 00:19:19.927
                 The king's army

247
00:19:19.929 --> 00:19:23.897
will come. hunt down
the hooded thieves.

248
00:19:23.899 --> 00:19:27.266
 No rock unturned until our shit
  holes are split on the cradle.

249
00:19:27.268 --> 00:19:28.333
              Mm.

250
00:19:29.836 --> 00:19:32.269
                     Your. uh...

251
00:19:32.271 --> 00:19:35.373
              your dark friend--
                    is he. um...

252
00:19:35.375 --> 00:19:37.108
            in our pope's grace?

253
00:19:37.110 --> 00:19:40.077
       A moor. converted
        in his homeland.

254
00:19:42.181 --> 00:19:44.414
  A good Catholic like us all.

255
00:19:45.550 --> 00:19:48.617
                Yea. Bloody work
                  is the Lord's.

256
00:19:48.619 --> 00:19:49.950
                          TORAN:
                         Indeed.

257
00:19:52.521 --> 00:19:54.654
         I need a name
      to offer my thanks.

258
00:19:54.656 --> 00:19:56.322
           Gruffudd.

259
00:19:56.324 --> 00:19:59.158
         You're the one
     they call "the wolf."

260
00:19:59.160 --> 00:20:01.160
                 I'm called many
                    hard things.

261
00:20:01.162 --> 00:20:02.561
                Most by my wife.

262
00:20:02.563 --> 00:20:05.196
    Thank you for answering
      our plea. Gruffudd.

263
00:20:05.198 --> 00:20:06.830
                   We serve each
                  other. friend.

264
00:20:06.832 --> 00:20:09.332
   The baron's forged weapons
    will be a welcome change

265
00:20:09.334 --> 00:20:11.367
        from our sticks
      and cobbled blades.

266
00:20:11.369 --> 00:20:13.235
        Ventris has lost
      nearly two legions.

267
00:20:13.237 --> 00:20:14.569
     His army is weakened.

268
00:20:14.571 --> 00:20:16.337
We're not ready to storm walls.

269
00:20:16.339 --> 00:20:17.905
    Even with noble swords.

270
00:20:17.907 --> 00:20:21.841
    But word of this victory
will spread and it will inspire.

271
00:20:21.843 --> 00:20:23.175
                     Our numbers
                      will grow.

272
00:20:23.177 --> 00:20:24.910
        I have no doubt.

273
00:20:24.912 --> 00:20:28.179
      Godspeed for your knight's
           return to sound body.

274
00:20:28.181 --> 00:20:30.514
                An unlikely ally
                   in our fight.

275
00:20:30.516 --> 00:20:32.516
              Let him know there
                 may come a time

276
00:20:32.518 --> 00:20:34.317
                  when I collect
                  on this favor.

277
00:20:43.394 --> 00:20:45.560
          Toran. Moor!

278
00:20:51.500 --> 00:20:53.099
                You crazy witch!

279
00:20:59.740 --> 00:21:01.239
          To what end

280
00:21:01.241 --> 00:21:03.307
does this devilry serve?

281
00:21:06.678 --> 00:21:08.744
           (grunting)

282
00:21:17.420 --> 00:21:19.386
         The baron has returned?

283
00:21:19.388 --> 00:21:22.389
No. But I have
news of his need.

284
00:21:22.391 --> 00:21:24.624
        At Heaven's Eye.
   we saw the rebel symbols.

285
00:21:24.626 --> 00:21:28.026
   Lord Ventris sent me back
     to secure more troops.

286
00:21:29.796 --> 00:21:32.296
     Sent you back? Alone?

287
00:21:32.298 --> 00:21:34.064
 Not to spare arms he may need.

288
00:21:34.066 --> 00:21:36.132
      I welcomed the risk
        of riding apart.

289
00:21:47.811 --> 00:21:50.411
 Gather what men we can spare.

290
00:21:50.413 --> 00:21:52.146
          With haste.

291
00:21:55.750 --> 00:21:57.649
Shall I find
the baroness?

292
00:21:57.651 --> 00:22:00.618
  No. You should find a bath.

293
00:22:00.620 --> 00:22:03.387
       You reek of shit.

294
00:22:03.389 --> 00:22:04.855
           And fear.

295
00:22:21.640 --> 00:22:23.706
            (sighs)

296
00:22:48.699 --> 00:22:50.765
            (groans)

297
00:22:56.271 --> 00:22:59.105
      You join the living.

298
00:22:59.107 --> 00:23:00.773
Who did this?

299
00:23:00.775 --> 00:23:03.041
                     The healer.

300
00:23:03.043 --> 00:23:05.109
     She offered no reason.

301
00:23:12.518 --> 00:23:14.017
            (groans)

302
00:23:35.206 --> 00:23:37.272
         Cut her binds.

303
00:23:50.687 --> 00:23:53.187
  Why did you cut and scar me?

304
00:23:53.189 --> 00:23:56.023
          To save you.

305
00:23:56.025 --> 00:23:58.425
                Your only chance

306
00:23:58.427 --> 00:24:01.294
to live is to be supposed dead.

307
00:24:03.564 --> 00:24:05.630
He gives you that gift.

308
00:24:24.016 --> 00:24:26.516
             Who are you. woman?

309
00:24:26.518 --> 00:24:28.351
                          Truly.

310
00:24:28.353 --> 00:24:31.420
                     What's your
                 interest in me?

311
00:24:34.057 --> 00:24:37.591
       You have a fate...

312
00:24:37.593 --> 00:24:39.693
  that you must learn to hold.

313
00:24:39.695 --> 00:24:44.631
One that will forever
mark your place in time.

314
00:24:46.601 --> 00:24:49.334
       I am here to help
        tell that story.

315
00:24:51.304 --> 00:24:53.370
       My story is over.

316
00:24:53.372 --> 00:24:55.238
No.

317
00:24:55.240 --> 00:24:58.708
It is just begun.

318
00:24:58.710 --> 00:25:01.944
   The angel spoke the truth.

319
00:25:05.882 --> 00:25:08.115
           The angel?

320
00:25:08.117 --> 00:25:11.350
        The bright child
        who came to you.

321
00:25:13.120 --> 00:25:14.853
             How...

322
00:25:16.790 --> 00:25:20.891
      I've never whispered
   a word of that to anyone.

323
00:25:22.895 --> 00:25:25.695
    I hear the same voices.

324
00:25:29.133 --> 00:25:33.067
     It's time to lay down
  this sword. Wilkin Brattle.

325
00:25:34.603 --> 00:25:36.769
(angel child's voice):
Your savior needs you

326
00:25:36.771 --> 00:25:40.038
        to live the life
      of a different man.

327
00:26:12.004 --> 00:26:14.004
              Unhitch one of the
                horses. brother.

328
00:26:14.006 --> 00:26:16.506
                Then go join the
            others at the caves.

329
00:26:16.508 --> 00:26:20.176
      I think I'll finish
       the ride. friend.

330
00:26:20.178 --> 00:26:22.911
  A plan hatched by a witch--
        what's to worry?

331
00:26:24.848 --> 00:26:29.516
       We deliver the dead. tell
         the tale. and ride off.

332
00:26:29.518 --> 00:26:32.185
              Free men. no price
                    on our head.

333
00:26:32.187 --> 00:26:34.020
            It's a sound devise.

334
00:26:34.022 --> 00:26:36.622
  Simple enough an executioner
     could carry it forth.

335
00:26:36.624 --> 00:26:38.624
                      (chuckles)

336
00:26:38.626 --> 00:26:40.792
                    And what say
                of your purpose.

337
00:26:40.794 --> 00:26:44.428
              What name for you?
                    Sneermonger?

338
00:26:46.465 --> 00:26:50.366
Well. my da. he wanted
to call me Marshal.

339
00:26:50.368 --> 00:26:53.068
But my ma thought it
too destined to war.

340
00:26:53.070 --> 00:26:56.004
                Ma got the name.
             da got the destiny.

341
00:26:56.006 --> 00:26:58.006
Yea. indeed.

342
00:26:58.008 --> 00:27:00.008
And what of your father?

343
00:27:00.010 --> 00:27:02.109
You never tell of anything.

344
00:27:04.746 --> 00:27:08.113
        There's nothing to tell.
               I don't have one.

345
00:27:10.884 --> 00:27:12.316
            (grunts)

346
00:27:14.720 --> 00:27:17.487
       (children's choir
      singing Latin hymn)

347
00:27:29.867 --> 00:27:32.300
        (choir continues
      singing Latin hymn)

348
00:27:51.520 --> 00:27:53.186
       (choir continues)

349
00:27:53.188 --> 00:27:54.687
ISABEL:
Pardon. Baroness.

350
00:27:54.689 --> 00:27:56.088
     (choir stops singing)

351
00:27:56.090 --> 00:27:57.722
      Outsiders have come.

352
00:27:57.724 --> 00:27:59.256
      They bring sad news.

353
00:28:14.405 --> 00:28:16.471
        Bring him down.

354
00:28:53.142 --> 00:28:56.309
    My deepest condolences.
           Lady Love.

355
00:28:56.311 --> 00:28:58.644
 Let's bring you and the baron
        into the castle

356
00:28:58.646 --> 00:29:00.712
   so you can mourn in peace.

357
00:29:11.290 --> 00:29:14.691
Have the baron taken
to the sacrament room.

358
00:29:25.003 --> 00:29:27.402
          Who are you?

359
00:29:30.340 --> 00:29:32.340
          Gawain Maddox. milady.

360
00:29:32.342 --> 00:29:36.343
              Punisher by trade.
         from the southern land.

361
00:29:36.345 --> 00:29:38.345
                This is Marshal.

362
00:29:38.347 --> 00:29:43.149
  a journey soldier-- he aids me
  in the capture of the accused.

363
00:29:43.151 --> 00:29:45.618
Tell me of his death.

364
00:29:45.620 --> 00:29:48.787
                We met the baron
                at Heaven's Eye.

365
00:29:48.789 --> 00:29:50.789
                  Called upon us
               to ride with him.

366
00:29:50.791 --> 00:29:52.323
            At the grass fields.

367
00:29:52.325 --> 00:29:54.625
             they crossed a band
              of hooded thieves.

368
00:29:54.627 --> 00:29:55.993
              Took a fierce run.

369
00:29:55.995 --> 00:29:58.662
       Noblemen cut down
       the seven of them.

370
00:29:58.664 --> 00:30:00.830
WILKIN:
Before the baron could rally.

371
00:30:00.832 --> 00:30:02.799
                rebels attacked.

372
00:30:02.801 --> 00:30:05.134
                     50 or more.

373
00:30:05.136 --> 00:30:08.770
Caught the ranks tired
and out of formation.

374
00:30:08.772 --> 00:30:12.840
Your husband fought gallantly.
but the numbers were too steep.

375
00:30:14.143 --> 00:30:15.842
                      I'm sorry.

376
00:30:19.947 --> 00:30:21.780
       Old men and boys.

377
00:30:21.782 --> 00:30:24.181
WILKIN: Your mail-clad soldiers
were too heavy to carry.

378
00:30:26.185 --> 00:30:28.919
We can send troops there
to collect the others.

379
00:30:28.921 --> 00:30:31.922
LADY LOVE: And what brings
an executioner to Ventrishire?

380
00:30:31.924 --> 00:30:33.790
         Work. milady.

381
00:30:33.792 --> 00:30:35.858
       I travel. go where
    my services are needed.

382
00:30:35.860 --> 00:30:37.925
                        RANDULF:
                        He lies!

383
00:30:39.929 --> 00:30:41.762
This man is
not the executioner.

384
00:30:43.766 --> 00:30:45.632
He's one of the thieves.

385
00:30:45.634 --> 00:30:47.200
        As is that one.

386
00:30:47.202 --> 00:30:50.102
           You're the liar. sir.

387
00:30:50.104 --> 00:30:53.371
I've traveled with Gawain
for many years.

388
00:30:53.373 --> 00:30:55.940
Dispatch a messenger
to Glamorgan for proof.

389
00:30:55.942 --> 00:30:58.809
          There is no other face
            looks like this one.

390
00:30:58.811 --> 00:31:01.111
                         WILKIN:
                    We just came

391
00:31:01.113 --> 00:31:03.046
to deliver the dead.

392
00:31:03.048 --> 00:31:05.048
Out of respect.

393
00:31:05.050 --> 00:31:07.016
We'll leave if it upsets
your court.

394
00:31:07.018 --> 00:31:10.519
 You'll stay and be quartered.

395
00:31:10.521 --> 00:31:13.888
  The remedy for this dispute
        is already here.

396
00:31:15.324 --> 00:31:17.490
     The wife and children
      of Maddox. sent here

397
00:31:17.492 --> 00:31:19.725
to wait for his return.

398
00:31:23.229 --> 00:31:25.628
         Come forward.

399
00:31:28.499 --> 00:31:30.899
              Tell us the truth.

400
00:31:30.901 --> 00:31:33.401
Is this man indeed your husband?

401
00:31:52.988 --> 00:31:55.054
           (fussing)

402
00:32:00.827 --> 00:32:02.726
             (trembling breaths)

403
00:32:02.728 --> 00:32:04.794
                     (whispers):
                      I'm sorry.

404
00:32:11.402 --> 00:32:13.468
My love.

405
00:32:16.005 --> 00:32:19.239
Good Maddy. thank God
you've come back safe.

406
00:32:23.911 --> 00:32:25.744
        This is lunacy!

407
00:32:25.746 --> 00:32:28.313
She conspires with him!

408
00:32:32.451 --> 00:32:35.385
        Such tragedy...

409
00:32:35.387 --> 00:32:37.854
   lands on my name this day.

410
00:32:43.628 --> 00:32:45.227
       My dearest friend.

411
00:32:45.229 --> 00:32:48.630
a life snuffed...

412
00:32:48.632 --> 00:32:51.199
not in a fitting battle...

413
00:32:52.402 --> 00:32:55.636
      ...but by the ambush
        of painted dogs.

414
00:32:58.073 --> 00:33:01.574
          And my kin.

415
00:33:01.576 --> 00:33:04.443
   Caught between two tales.

416
00:33:04.445 --> 00:33:06.311
      I speak only truth.
         dear brother.

417
00:33:06.313 --> 00:33:08.980
     I have nothing to gain
        from such a lie.

418
00:33:08.982 --> 00:33:11.215
         These men are
    the bandits we pursued.

419
00:33:11.217 --> 00:33:13.217
               Did battle in the
          fields beyond the eye.

420
00:33:13.219 --> 00:33:16.220
            I myself
   and other honored knights

421
00:33:16.222 --> 00:33:18.255
         heard you tell
    how you were dispatched

422
00:33:18.257 --> 00:33:20.857
     <i> before</i> any such fray.

423
00:33:24.595 --> 00:33:26.094
              Yea.

424
00:33:26.096 --> 00:33:28.429
         I did. but...
WILKIN: You may have

425
00:33:28.431 --> 00:33:32.399
            nothing to gain. but
            you've much to hide.

426
00:33:32.401 --> 00:33:36.069
  We saw this man at the fray.

427
00:33:36.071 --> 00:33:39.072
  He tucked tail and slithered
   away. letting his brothers

428
00:33:39.074 --> 00:33:42.275
fall to the curs.

429
00:33:42.277 --> 00:33:44.477
             That's why he lies.

430
00:33:44.479 --> 00:33:45.978
'Cause we know
the truth.

431
00:33:45.980 --> 00:33:47.446
           That's...

432
00:33:47.448 --> 00:33:49.514
  I tell you. these are the...
CORBETT: Enough!

433
00:34:00.993 --> 00:34:03.660
       So. then. Reeve...

434
00:34:03.662 --> 00:34:06.996
 you are either a false accuser

435
00:34:06.998 --> 00:34:09.398
 or you deserted your commander
           in battle!

436
00:34:11.335 --> 00:34:14.268
         Both come with
     a punishment of death!

437
00:34:16.338 --> 00:34:18.838
         (whispering):
           Please...

438
00:34:18.840 --> 00:34:20.773
            Milus...

439
00:34:20.775 --> 00:34:22.341
           brother...

440
00:34:22.343 --> 00:34:23.842
                 do not do this.

441
00:34:23.844 --> 00:34:25.443
           Take him!

442
00:34:25.445 --> 00:34:27.111
          Brother. we are blood.

443
00:34:27.113 --> 00:34:28.846
               Do not betray me.
                       Damn you!

444
00:34:28.848 --> 00:34:30.347
     Damn your half-hatred!

445
00:34:30.349 --> 00:34:31.514
                       Damn y...

446
00:34:31.516 --> 00:34:32.348
            (grunts)

447
00:34:32.350 --> 00:34:34.316
(gasping)

448
00:34:34.318 --> 00:34:36.051
                 (Randulf yells)

449
00:34:36.053 --> 00:34:38.820
        (Randulf shouts)

450
00:34:38.822 --> 00:34:40.154
Curse you!

451
00:34:40.156 --> 00:34:41.688
I'll curse you
from hell!

452
00:34:41.690 --> 00:34:43.589
               (Randulf sobbing)

453
00:34:51.665 --> 00:34:55.098
                My shame is only
          outdone by my sadness.

454
00:34:57.068 --> 00:35:00.369
My deepest sympathies. Baroness.

455
00:35:00.371 --> 00:35:03.939
     I am in your service.
       whatever the need.

456
00:35:05.509 --> 00:35:07.641
       Thank you. Milus.

457
00:35:09.678 --> 00:35:12.611
        I will do haste
   with manor law and trial.

458
00:35:14.681 --> 00:35:16.347
        It is fitting...

459
00:35:16.349 --> 00:35:18.482
that the man falsely accused

460
00:35:18.484 --> 00:35:22.085
be the one who is skilled
to take his head.

461
00:35:33.497 --> 00:35:36.931
      Welcome to Castle Ventris.
                    executioner.

462
00:36:12.100 --> 00:36:14.300
                       Baroness.

463
00:36:14.302 --> 00:36:17.136
     The priest. he said I could
        come for evening prayer.

464
00:36:17.138 --> 00:36:18.770
          Please. sit.

465
00:36:18.772 --> 00:36:20.805
  I welcome the chapel's use.

466
00:36:20.807 --> 00:36:23.774
  Few spend time here but me.

467
00:36:27.446 --> 00:36:29.512
          Do you mind?

468
00:36:31.315 --> 00:36:33.014
            Please.

469
00:36:41.957 --> 00:36:43.990
        I wouldn't think

470
00:36:43.992 --> 00:36:47.559
    one of your trade would
 complicate things with prayer.

471
00:36:49.996 --> 00:36:53.364
Perhaps it takes you
in deeper.

472
00:36:58.269 --> 00:37:01.236
                   May I ask how
                  this happened?

473
00:37:03.340 --> 00:37:05.673
It was given to me
by a healer.

474
00:37:05.675 --> 00:37:08.842
A holy woman.

475
00:37:08.844 --> 00:37:11.343
A reminder
of my need for faith.

476
00:37:13.780 --> 00:37:15.846
               Your soldier gave
                  the impression

477
00:37:15.848 --> 00:37:17.848
                it distinguished
              you for some time.

478
00:37:17.850 --> 00:37:21.318
      Yet. the burn looks fresh.

479
00:37:21.320 --> 00:37:24.154
I renew the vow
when my faith wavers.

480
00:37:28.092 --> 00:37:30.492
                You're bleeding.

481
00:37:30.494 --> 00:37:32.927
    Yea.

482
00:37:32.929 --> 00:37:36.330
An angry branch
on last night's ride.

483
00:37:36.332 --> 00:37:38.832
                          May I?

484
00:37:38.834 --> 00:37:41.167
                         WILKIN:
                In here. milady?

485
00:37:41.169 --> 00:37:42.835
                      LADY LOVE:
                   No better one

486
00:37:42.837 --> 00:37:45.237
           to heal you than Him.

487
00:37:56.015 --> 00:37:58.515
                   The physicker
            should look at this.

488
00:38:01.386 --> 00:38:05.921
         (baby crying)

489
00:38:18.068 --> 00:38:20.535
I'll find the physicker.

490
00:38:20.537 --> 00:38:23.905
                 No. Stay.

491
00:38:23.907 --> 00:38:25.706
           Finish your devotion.

492
00:38:25.708 --> 00:38:28.909
         I'll have him find you.

493
00:38:55.069 --> 00:38:58.837
            Baroness?

494
00:38:58.839 --> 00:39:02.040
I sent an emissary
to London

495
00:39:02.042 --> 00:39:07.010
and one to Erik's brother
in Coventry.

496
00:39:07.012 --> 00:39:12.048
I'm sure our king will offer
comfort and guidance

497
00:39:12.050 --> 00:39:14.617
of how we proceed
to govern.

498
00:39:14.619 --> 00:39:17.954
                   We proceed by
             burying my husband.

499
00:39:19.123 --> 00:39:21.456
              Yes.

500
00:39:21.458 --> 00:39:23.691
           Of course.

501
00:39:25.795 --> 00:39:28.195
        Another thought.

502
00:39:28.197 --> 00:39:30.197
my lady.

503
00:39:30.199 --> 00:39:33.533
This executioner--

504
00:39:33.535 --> 00:39:35.535
his arrival.

505
00:39:35.537 --> 00:39:39.038
although it brought sadness--

506
00:39:39.040 --> 00:39:41.373
it could turn
to good fortune.

507
00:39:41.375 --> 00:39:42.807
                    How so?

508
00:39:42.809 --> 00:39:45.376
If we secure him
and his soldier.

509
00:39:45.378 --> 00:39:48.379
we gain skilled men
to hunt offenders

510
00:39:48.381 --> 00:39:50.714
and carry out the correction.

511
00:39:50.716 --> 00:39:55.218
Sends a sound message.

512
00:39:55.220 --> 00:39:58.654
      Ventrishire will not
      suffer lawlessness.

513
00:40:01.492 --> 00:40:04.993
      That's well advised.
       dear Chamberlain.

514
00:40:04.995 --> 00:40:07.895
  Good. I'll draft the letters

515
00:40:07.897 --> 00:40:10.330
that bind them.

516
00:40:29.383 --> 00:40:33.451
I have news. Maddox.

517
00:40:34.954 --> 00:40:39.122
The trial was swift.
the guilt clear.

518
00:40:40.592 --> 00:40:43.059
We will stage the execution
in the village square

519
00:40:43.061 --> 00:40:45.494
midday tomorrow.

520
00:40:51.568 --> 00:40:54.268
        He's your blood.

521
00:40:54.270 --> 00:40:56.703
     There must be some...

522
00:40:56.705 --> 00:41:00.073
due leniency. a brother's mercy?

523
00:41:00.075 --> 00:41:02.542
    You rid me of a mistake

524
00:41:02.544 --> 00:41:07.012
 influenced by familial guilt.

525
00:41:08.615 --> 00:41:12.483
      No kin. no worries.

526
00:41:14.253 --> 00:41:17.053
         But of course.
 you wouldn't understand that.

527
00:41:17.055 --> 00:41:20.723
      Being a family man.

528
00:41:20.725 --> 00:41:23.825
   And you're the final word
        of justice here?

529
00:41:26.262 --> 00:41:29.596
     As well as chancellor
          and advisor.

530
00:41:29.598 --> 00:41:33.266
You'll find that nothing passes

531
00:41:33.268 --> 00:41:36.736
       through this shire
    without me touching it.

532
00:41:36.738 --> 00:41:39.171
   I'm afraid that's a lesson
       I'll have to miss.

533
00:41:39.173 --> 00:41:41.173
   I move on after tomorrow.

534
00:41:41.175 --> 00:41:43.341
Ah. but that's my news.

535
00:41:43.343 --> 00:41:47.577
      You and your soldier
         will stay on.

536
00:41:47.579 --> 00:41:50.146
 Your position is now standing.

537
00:41:54.685 --> 00:41:57.085
       We're journeyman.

538
00:41:57.087 --> 00:41:58.953
                      Travelers.

539
00:41:58.955 --> 00:42:00.754
     Now. you have a home.

540
00:42:00.756 --> 00:42:04.857
I'm sure that will be
a comfort to your

541
00:42:04.859 --> 00:42:07.993
      wife and wee things.

542
00:42:11.698 --> 00:42:14.231
       (breathing loudly)

543
00:42:21.707 --> 00:42:24.206
    Why are you doing this?

544
00:42:26.810 --> 00:42:29.677
Our buried truths bind us.

545
00:42:29.679 --> 00:42:32.713
And your skills
will serve me.

546
00:42:38.853 --> 00:42:41.320
I need a man

547
00:42:41.322 --> 00:42:43.722
with the heart
of a dragon.

548
00:43:08.148 --> 00:43:10.614
          (scratching)

549
00:43:12.718 --> 00:43:15.284
          (soft gasp)

550
00:43:17.488 --> 00:43:19.955
ANNORA:
Ludwig?

551
00:43:31.567 --> 00:43:33.967
      (shallow breathing)

552
00:43:47.381 --> 00:43:51.116
We need to ready our faith.

553
00:43:51.118 --> 00:43:56.020
                     (shakily):
               <i> Ja. meine Liebe.</i>

554
00:44:02.093 --> 00:44:04.493
             (breathing shakily)

555
00:44:22.545 --> 00:44:25.412
 FATHER:<i> Dominus noster Jesus
Christus te absolvat. </i> (groans)

556
00:44:25.414 --> 00:44:27.947
        <i> Ego auctoritate</i>

557
00:44:27.949 --> 00:44:31.116
       <i> ipsius te absolvo</i>

558
00:44:31.118 --> 00:44:35.453
 <i> ab omni vinculo</i>
<i> excommunicationis</i> <i> et interdicti</i>

559
00:44:35.455 --> 00:44:38.556
 (boys singing chant in Latin)
              <i> in quantum possum</i>

560
00:44:38.558 --> 00:44:41.458
                <i> et tu indiges. </i>
           (groaning)

561
00:44:41.460 --> 00:44:44.727
                 <i> Ego te absolvo</i>

562
00:44:44.729 --> 00:44:47.763
        <i> a peccatis tuis</i>

563
00:44:47.765 --> 00:44:50.565
              <i> in nomine Patris.</i>
                      <i> et Filii.</i>

564
00:44:50.567 --> 00:44:52.366
   <i> et Spiritus Sancti. Amen.</i>

565
00:44:56.905 --> 00:45:00.006
              (Randulf groaning)

566
00:45:06.446 --> 00:45:08.879
   (singing chant continues)

567
00:45:14.619 --> 00:45:17.019
 Blades have been grinded. sir.

568
00:45:26.296 --> 00:45:28.696
        (groans softly)

569
00:45:46.681 --> 00:45:49.181
        (groans softly)

570
00:45:55.621 --> 00:45:58.054
   (singing chant continues)

571
00:46:02.727 --> 00:46:05.561
     (whispering. laughing)

572
00:46:05.563 --> 00:46:08.030
        (inhales deeply)

573
00:46:08.032 --> 00:46:10.032
        (exhales deeply)

574
00:46:10.034 --> 00:46:12.467
           (quietly):
            Help me.

575
00:46:15.705 --> 00:46:18.272
       (crowd murmuring)

576
00:46:59.381 --> 00:47:03.149
            Always.

577
00:47:17.565 --> 00:47:19.064
  You'll need this. headsman.

578
00:47:19.066 --> 00:47:21.900
Little Rand
was full of shit.

579
00:47:21.902 --> 00:47:23.768
           (laughter)

580
00:47:23.770 --> 00:47:26.070
                A stuffed clown.

581
00:47:26.072 --> 00:47:28.405
           (laughter)

582
00:47:28.407 --> 00:47:29.906
You best take another.

583
00:47:29.908 --> 00:47:31.741
    Yeah. His ass will spout
        like a fountain.

584
00:47:31.743 --> 00:47:34.410
           (laughter)

585
00:47:34.412 --> 00:47:35.944
Who did you spring from?

586
00:47:35.946 --> 00:47:38.146
           (laughter)

587
00:48:02.638 --> 00:48:04.704
                       (yelling)

588
00:48:05.640 --> 00:48:09.508
           (thudding)

589
00:48:09.510 --> 00:48:12.043
